dded to the image of California as a destination for ambitious dreamers, an image that prevails to this day. In bringing together a range of art and archival material such as artists' diaries and contemporary newspaper articles, The Art of the Gold Rush broadens our understanding of American culture during a memorable period in the nation's history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aArt, AmericanzCaliforniay19th centuryvExhibitions. 0aGold mines and mining in art. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  a1800s.  a19th century.  aacademic.  aambition.  aamerican culture.  aamerican history.  aartistic.  aartists.  acalifornia history.  acalifornia.  acultural history.  acultural studies.  afolk art.  afolklore.  aget rich.  agold rush.  agold.  agolden state.  aimagination.  amyth.  apaintings.  aprospector.  ascholarly.  asocial change.  asocial history.  asocial studies.  asunday morning in the mines.  asutters mill.  athrill seeking.  aunited states history.  aus history.1 aDriesbach, Janice T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolland, Katherine Church, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHolland, Katherine Church, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Harvey L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJones, Harvey L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093515040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520935150423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520935150/original  a978